starbucks-how-to-get-a-free-red-cup-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ERed%20Cup%20Day%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20when%20Starbucks%2C%20which%20is%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20a%20massive%20turnaround%20campaign%2C%20usually%20gives%20away%20reusable%20cups%20and%20rakes%20in%20record%20sales%20%E2%80%94%20but%20instead%2C%20thousands%20of%20baristas%20are%20walking%20off%20the%20job%2C%20in%20hopes%20that%20the%20coffee%20giant%20sits%20down%20to%20finalize%20their%20first%20contract.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBaristas%20at%20more%20than%2065%20stores%20across%2040%20US%20cities%20launched%20their%20strike%20on%20Thursday%2C%20disrupting%20the%20historically%20major%20sales%20promotion.%20In%202024%2C%20Red%20Cup%20Day%20at%20Starbucks%20drove%20a%2042.4%25%20spike%20in%20daily%20visits%20relative%20to%20an%20average%20Thursday%2C%20according%20to%20foot%20traffic%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.placer.ai%2Fanchor%2Farticles%2Fstarbucks-red-cup-day-makes-a-comeback%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Placer.ai.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkers%20at%20more%20than%20550%20union%20stores%20are%20prepared%20to%20join%20the%20strike%20if%20negotiations%20don't%20resume%2C%20according%20to%20a%20statement%20from%20the%20union.%20The%20work%20stoppage%20marks%20the%20fourth%20strike%20the%20union%20has%20organized%20since%202023%2C%20and%20the%20third%20work%20stoppage%20since%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-office-near-brian-niccol-newport-beach-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECEO%20Brian%20Niccol%3C%2Fa%3E%20took%20the%20helm%20of%20the%20company%20in%20September%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20disappointed%20that%20Workers%20United%2C%20who%20represents%20less%20than%204%25%20of%20our%20partners%2C%20has%20called%20for%20a%20strike%20instead%20of%20returning%20to%20the%20bargaining%20table%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Starbucks%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20adding%20that%20less%20than%201%25%20of%20the%20company's%20store%20locations%20are%20being%20affected.%20The%20company%20has%2016%2C864%20stores%20across%20the%20US%2C%20according%20to%20its%20most%20recent%20financial%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20workers%20have%20been%20trying%20to%20ratify%20their%20collective%20bargaining%20agreement%20since%20the%20first%20store%20unionized%20in%20December%202021.%20After%20some%20progress%20and%20a%20commitment%20by%20the%20company%20to%20reach%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-says-wants-reach-deal-union-workers-united-ratify-contract-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elabor%20agreement%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20end%20of%202024%2C%20contract%20talks%20collapsed%20last%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStarbucks%20corporate%20and%20the%20unionized%20workers%20have%20each%20blamed%20the%20other%20for%20the%20breakdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20been%20very%20clear%20%E2%80%94%20when%20the%20union%20is%20ready%20to%20come%20back%20to%20the%20bargaining%20table%2C%20we're%20ready%20to%20talk%2C%26quot%3B%20Starbucks'%20spokesperson%20said%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20union%20insists%20it's%20ready%20to%20bargain%20and%20is%20waiting%20on%20Starbucks%20to%20return%20to%20the%20table%20with%20new%20economic%20proposals%20and%20solutions%20to%20more%20than%20700%20unresolved%20unfair%20labor%20practice%20charges%20related%20to%20allegations%20of%20retaliation%20and%20union%20busting%2C%20according%20to%20a%20statement%20from%20Starbucks%20Workers%20United.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fa6d5345-ea34-41a8-ad9c-14fc73a8721e%5C%22%3EBaristas%20prepare%20for%20a%20bitter%2C%20public%20battle%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20strike%20comes%20a%20little%20more%20than%20a%20month%20after%20the%20company%20initiated%20a%20%241%20billion%20restructuring%20as%20part%20of%20its%20%26quot%3BBack%20to%20Starbucks%26quot%3B%20revitalization%20effort.%20The%20September%20restructuring%20involved%20the%20closure%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flist-of-closing-starbucks-locations-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emore%20than%20600%20stores%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20layoff%20of%20thousands%20of%20baristas%20and%20the%20elimination%20of%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-north-american-store-closures-lay-off-employees-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E900%20non-retail%20jobs.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20union%20reported%20an%20increased%20interest%20in%20stores%20joining%20its%20ranks%20since%20the%20restructuring.%20However%2C%20since%20the%20beginning%20of%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20term%20in%20January%2C%20the%20National%20Labor%20Relations%20Board%2C%C2%A0which%20certifies%20union%20elections%2C%20has%20not%20been%20fully%20staffed%20with%20the%20minimum%20number%20of%20members%20needed%20to%20officially%20issue%20decisions%20or%20take%20formal%20actions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20any%20new%20votes%20to%20unionize%20additional%20stores%20have%20remained%20in%20limbo%2C%20and%20their%20baristas%20have%20been%20without%20the%20full%20protection%20of%20the%20National%20Labor%20Relations%20Act%2C%20a%20federal%20law%20that%20dictates%20the%20rights%20of%20unionized%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-policy-crack-down-barista-notes-cups-coaching-termination-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EStarbucks%20baristas%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20were%20not%20recognized%20as%20part%20of%20the%20union%20prior%20to%20January%20cannot%20join%20in%20on%20the%20strike%2C%20even%20if%20they%20have%20since%20voted%20to%20be%20officially%20recognized%2C%20Cathy%20Creighton%2C%20a%20former%20field%20attorney%20for%20the%20National%20Labor%20Relations%20Board%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20low%20density%20of%20unionized%20stores%20compared