usinessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fsecurities-and-exchange-commission%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESecurities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%3C%2Fa%3E%20now%20caution%20investors%20that%20the%20technology%20could%20have%20a%20significant%20negative%20impact%20on%20their%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%20this%20year%2C%20418%20publicly%20traded%20companies%20valued%20at%20more%20than%20%241%20billion%20have%20cited%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffortune-500-companies-ai-regulation-risk-factor-business-annual-reports-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI-related%20risk%20factors%3C%2Fa%3E%20associated%20with%20reputational%20harm%20in%20those%20reports%2C%20according%20to%20an%20analysis%20conducted%20with%20AlphaSense%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20That%20is%20a%2046%25%20jump%20from%202024%20and%20roughly%20nine%20times%20greater%20than%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20datasets%20could%20hurt%20a%20company's%20image%2C%20the%20filings%20say%2C%20by%20producing%20biased%20or%20incorrect%20information%2C%20compromising%20security%2C%20or%20infringing%20on%20others'%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20Take-Two%20Interactive%20Software%20highlighted%20AI%20as%20a%20risk%20factor%20in%20its%202024%20filing%20with%20the%20SEC%20and%20expanded%20that%20disclosure%20with%20more%20than%20double%20the%20number%20of%20words%20in%20its%202025%20filing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20of%20us%20are%20using%20AI%20today%20in%20a%20way%20that's%20greater%20than%20we%20used%20it%20a%20year%20ago%20and%20greater%20than%20the%20year%20before%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20video-game%20maker's%20CEO%2C%20Strauss%20Zelnick%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWith%20more%20usage%2C%20more%20experimentation%2C%20and%20more%20implementation%2C%20there's%20the%20potential%20for%20more%20risk%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20taking%20these%20steps%20span%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20industries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Visa's%20SEC%20filing%20earlier%20this%20month%20says%20that%20as%20the%20financial%20services%20company%20scales%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvisa-launches-ai-powered-creator-financial-tools-startup-karat-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Euse%20of%20agentic%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20commerce%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20may%20see%20increased%20instances%20of%20erroneous%20or%20disputed%20payments%2C%20increased%20chargebacks%20and%20reputational%20harm.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsumer-products%20manufacturer%20Clorox%20noted%20in%20its%20August%20report%20that%20AI%20tools%20%26quot%3Bmay%20compromise%20confidential%20or%20sensitive%20information%2C%26quot%3B%20while%20cosmetics%20brand%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felf-obsessed-hailey-bieber-rhode-billion-dollar-acquisiton-earnings-revenue-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EELF%20Beauty%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20in%20a%20May%20filing%20that%20its%20%26quot%3Bability%20to%20adapt%20to%20new%20regulations%2C%20technological%20shifts%2C%20ethical%20standards%2C%20and%20stakeholder%20expectations%20regarding%20AI%20may%20materially%20impact%20our%20operations%2C%20financial%20condition%2C%20or%20reputation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dccc25b3-c45a-4476-9c14-1f41d576adb1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Known%20unknowns'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20are%20legally%20required%20to%20update%20risk%20factors%20in%20their%20SEC%20filings%20when%20new%2C%20material%20risks%20emerge%20or%20existing%20ones%20change.%20The%20goal%20is%20to%20%26quot%3Bscare%20investors%26quot%3B%20into%20understanding%20what%20could%20materially%20harm%20the%20company%2C%20which%20is%20an%20intentional%20feature%20of%20the%20system%2C%20said%20M.%20Todd%20Henderson%2C%20a%20law%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago%20Law%20School.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou've%20got%20to%20disclose%20known%20unknowns%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20adding%20warnings%20about%20AI%20to%20their%20filings%2C%20company%20leaders%20are%20showing%20that%20they%20consider%20the%20technology's%20potential%20impact%20as%20a%20serious%20matter%2C%20said%20Henderson%2C%20possibly%20even%20more%20so%20than%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20internet%20in%20the%20late%201990s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20then%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20disclosures%20were%20cautious%20optimism%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20internet%20also%20seemed%20to%20pose%20a%20threat%20only%20to%20retailers%20and%20print%20publishers%2C%20and%20not%20to%20most%20other%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20AI%2C%20the%20warnings%20are%20much%20starker%2C%20and%20companies%20across%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20industries%20caution%20that%20it%20could%20result%20in%20grave%20outcomes%2C%20said%20Henderson.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLosing%20your%20data%20in%20a%20hack%20is%20one%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20if%20you%20deploy%20AI%20and%20it%20hallucinates%2C%20that's%20potentially%20a%20much%20bigger%20problem.%20Bad%20medical%20diagnoses%2C%20legal%20advice%2C%20or%20engineering%20conclusions%20could%20cause%20mistakes%20that%20threaten%20the%20core%20of%20the%20business.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkpmg-trust-in-ai-study-2025-how-employees-use-ai-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EEmployee%20misuse%20of%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20also%20lead%20to%20trouble.%20Some%2066%25%20of%20workers%20have%20relied%20on%20AI%20output%20without%20critically%20evaluating%20the%20information%20it%20provides%2C%20and%2072%25%20have%20put%20less%20effort%20into%20their%20work%20due%20to%20AI%2C%20according%20to%20a%20global%20survey%20of%2032%2C352%20workers%20between%20November%202024%20and%20January%202025%20that%20was%20conducted%20by%20accounting%20firm%20KPMG%20and%20the%20University%20of%20Melbourne.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22981986ec-80c7-44df-ba3b-55c196e70e2c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EValue%20trumps%20risk%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20risks%20associated%20with%20AI%2C%20companies%20still%20see%20significant%20value%20in%20the%20technology's%20potential%20to%20boost%20productivity.%20Many%20are%20racing%20to%20invest%20in%20the%20technology.%20The%20average%20total%20AI%20spend%20roughly%20doubled%20in%202024%20from%20the%20previous%20year%20to%20%2410.3%20million%2C%20according%20to%20Bain%20%26amp%3B%20Co.%20The%20management%20consulting%20firm%20looked%20at%20companies%20with%20annual%20revenues%20ranging%20from%20%2450%20million%20to%20over%20%245%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Take-Two%2C%20Zelnick%20said%20AI%20is%20helping%20the%20video-game%20maker's%20workers%20be%20more%20efficient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we're%20doing%20is%20reducing%20the%20weight%20of%20mundane%20work%20and%20allowing%20people%20to%20spend%20their%20time%20and%20brainpower%20on%20more%20interesting%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BFor%20example%2C%20we've%20had%20levels%20within%20mobile%20games%20that%20were%20created%20largely%20by%20AI.%20That's%20new%2C%20and%20that%20wasn't%20the%20case%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20ago.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20%26quot%3BGrand%20Theft%20Auto%26quot%3B%20boss%20still%20recognizes%20AI's%20potential%20downsides%2C%20he%20said%20that%20not%20using%20the%20technology%20would%20be%20dicey%2C%20too%20%E2%80%94%20a%20conundrum%20reflected%20in%20many%20companies'%20SEC%20filings%2C%20including%20Take-Two's.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20failure%20to%20adopt%20new%20technology%20could%20put%20you%20at%20risk%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Zelnick.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-are-warning-about-risks-of-ai-sec-filings-2025-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1763031481000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22http