way%20access%2C%20Business%20Insider%20found.%20There%20were%20no%20notable%20incidents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20has%20long%20been%20vocal%20about%20his%20stance%20against%20lidar%20%E2%80%94%20a%20type%20of%20sensor%20that%20shoots%20laser%20light%20to%20measure%20the%20distance%20to%20objects.%20While%20Tesla%20uses%20lidar%20for%20internal%20testing%2C%20Musk%20has%20said%20that%20the%20sensor%20is%20an%20expensive%20%26quot%3Bcrutch%26quot%3B%20that%20could%20get%20in%20the%20way%20of%20effectively%20scaling%20robotaxis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnyone%20relying%20on%20lidar%20is%20doomed%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%2C%20for%20his%20part%2C%20is%20not%20making%20up%20claims%20about%20sensors%20providing%20conflicting%20readings%20of%20the%20real-world%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWaymo%20employees%20themselves%20acknowledged%20in%20one%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fabs%2F2210.09267%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2022%20research%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20need%20to%20address%20the%20%26quot%3Bambiguity%26quot%3B%20between%20the%20input%20from%20camera%20and%20radar%20sensors.%20However%2C%20that%20same%20paper%20explores%20a%20method%20that%20could%20mitigate%20%E2%80%94%20but%20not%20completely%20solve%20%E2%80%94%20the%20ambiguity%20in%20part%20by%20having%20the%20radar%20essentially%20double-check%20and%20refine%20the%20camera's%20distance%20estimates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20and%20a%20Tesla%20spokesperson%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Tesla%20CEO%20may%20be%20quick%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-waymo-diss-john-krafcik-robotaxi-wars-cybercab-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edismiss%20Waymo's%20progress%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20he%20has%20also%20given%20the%20company%20its%20flowers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-shareholder-meeting-elon-musk-pay-pa